---
description: Safe backend and infrastructure rules
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json,sql,yml,yaml}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

This app uses its own backend/infrastructure, not managed backend templates.

Rules:
- do not expose secrets in client code
- do not hardcode server credentials
- do not hardcode Neon credentials
- do not hardcode Bunny Storage secrets
- do not hardcode LiveKit secret keys
- do not move secure server logic into client code
- do not fake backend success with local-only state
- do not replace real API/database/live logic with placeholders unless explicitly asked
- do not weaken auth, permissions, or transaction safety

Infrastructure constraints:
- preserve current Hetzner deployment assumptions
- preserve Coolify deployment flow
- preserve Neon database integrity
- preserve Bunny Storage media flow
- preserve LiveKit integration flow

Forbidden:
- do not replatform to Supabase, Apwrite, Railway, DigitalOcean, Ghost, Netlify, or similar providers
- do not introduce provider-specific code for unused services
- do not create fake backend helpers that hide real failures

Default behavior:
keep business logic and infrastructure aligned with the real production stack.
